The Gashuku Uganda competition will be held on May 4-8 at Lugogo Indoor Arena on May 30. Joint training will be held in Mbita in Homa Bay County and will be followed by national karate grading for senior players on June 9. On June 20, the annual junior championships will be held at Parklands Club in Nairobi.     The 2021 Japan Karate Association of Kenya (JKA-Kenya) calendar will kick off on January 25 at Goan Gymkhana Club in Nairobi with a joint training of all grades.
JKA-Kenya Caleb Atemi Chairperson Caleb Atemi told Nation Sport that the training will be followed by a referees and judges’ course which will also be held at the same club on February 8 as the association steps up efforts this year to increase the number of technical officials.



